KCCAns:
Recommended for the crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root initiation: 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage: 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

Providing bottom and side ventilations for free and faster air circulation and to avoid formation of hot and humid pockets between the onion layers.  Avoid direct sunlight or rain water falling on onion bulbs to reduce sun scald, fading of colour and quality deterioration.  Maintenance of stacking height to avoid pressure bruising. Periodical disinfection of structures and premises to check rottage.

KCCAns:
Recommended for the crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root initiation: 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage: 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

Recommended  for The crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root intiation : 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage : 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage : 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage : 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

KCCAns:
Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

Rattanidhi sampling aggregation method-

1- Visit the field in which the sampling is to be done by jig-jig and mark it at 10-15 places so that all parts of the farm can be included in it.

2- Remove debris, debris etc. from the upper surface on the selected places.

3- 15 cm at all these places (6-9 inch) dig deeper V shaped cord. Cleansing the pot from the top of the scalp, up to 2 cm from the top. Remove the thick soil from the bottom and put it in a clean bucket or tray.

4- Mix the collected clay well with the hands and put on clean clothes and make a round pile. Remove the clay from the finger to the four equal parts and remove the soil separately. Now mix the remaining two parts again and make the rounds. Repeat this procedure till almost half of the remains are left in the soil. This representative will be sample.

5- Keep the dry soil sample in a clean plastic bag and put it in a garment bag. An information sheet along with the sample on which all the information is written, put it in a plastic bag and outside the clothes bag.

6- Now send these prepared samples to the soil testing laboratory.

The action of chemical action and microbes in the stomach of earthworms increases the availability of nitrogen, phosphor and potash and other subtle elements found in the soil. Vermi compost does not contain stench and flies and mosquitoes do not grow and the atmosphere is not polluted. By controlling the temperature, the bacteria are active and active. Preparation Method:

The fertilizer is to be made from the waste, from which the pieces of glass and metal pieces are separated properly and after this, the platform of 10x4 feet is prepared to prepare the Vermi compost up to 6 to 12 inches high. 2 ridges are added to this platform and huts are made for shade above the platform. Keep in mind that due to excessive wetness the air will be blocked and the microbes and earthworms will not be able to die or work.

After 45 days irrigation is stopped and jute bags are removed. After removing the brood, the top manure dries up and the earthworms go into humidity below. The manure taken from the strains is dried and filtered in shade and stored in a shady place. The quantity of Vermi compost requires 100 grams, one kilogram of one year plants and 6-8 quintals per acre in the crop. Using Vermicum Wash, it would be good to have two exhaust drains on the platform so that the worm wash can be collected.

KCCAns:
he fertilizer is to be made from the waste, from which the pieces of glass and metal pieces are separated properly and after this, the platform of 10x4 feet is prepared to prepare the Vermi compost up to 6 to 12 inches high. 2 ridges are added to this platform and huts are made for shade above the platform. Dry fodder on the platform, fertilize 3-4 quintals of cow dung and 7-8 quintals of garbage (Garvage) Which gets irrigated by sapling for 10-15 days so that the temperature of the compost can be reduced. After this, 100 thousand square feet are left to the extent of 10 thousand earthworms. After leaving the ketchu, the stitches are covered with jute sacks, and they keep irrigation for 4 days so that 45-50 percent moisture is maintained. Keep in mind that due to excessive wetness the air will be blocked and the microbes and earthworms will not be able to die or work.

After 45 days irrigation is stopped and jute bags are removed. After removing the brood, the top manure dries up and the earthworms go into humidity below. Then separate the dry Vermic compost of the above. After 4-5 days, the upper manure of the stitches is dried and the dry manure is separated from the top. In this way, the entire compost separates from the stitches in 3-4 times and the earthworms are left in the last In the stitches in 2 months, the number of earthworms inserted doubles, keep in mind that do not use gantry, spade or cranberries to remove manure from hand. The manure taken from the strains is dried and filtered in shade and stored in a shady place. The quantity of Vermi compost requires 100 grams, one kilogram of one year plants and 6-8 quintals per acre in the crop. Using Vermicum Wash, it would be good to have two exhaust drains on the platform so that the worm wash can be collected.

Then separate the dry Vermic compost of the above. After 4-5 days, the upper manure of the stitches is dried and the dry manure is separated from the top. In this way, the entire compost separates from the stitches in 3-4 times and the earthworms are left in the last In the stitches in 2 months, the number of earthworms inserted doubles, keep in mind that do not use gantry, spade or cranberries to remove manure from hand. The manure taken from the strains is dried and filtered in shade and stored in a shady place. The quantity of Vermi compost requires 100 grams, one kilogram of one year plants and 6-8 quintals per acre in the crop. Using Vermicum Wash, it would be good to have two exhaust drains on the platform so that the worm wash can be collected.

Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

Varieties--Gurguva aloe   -    Aloe vera (Aloe barbadensis),

Certain other types like Zanzibar, Uganda, Natal and Hyderabad aloe are having good quality of “aloe gel”. Soil and Climate--Well drained laterite to loamy soils is suited for aloe cultivation. The soil pH must be ranged from 7.0 to 8.5. Commercial cultivation can be done in regions having 25 – 40°C.Seed and sowing---It is propagated through suckers. The suckers are dipped in 0.1 % Carbendazim for five minutes and planted in the field. For planting one hectare of land, 10,000 suckers are required.Planting season---The planting can be done during two seasons namely June – July and September – October.Planting---Field is thoroughly ploughed and beds of suitable sizes are formed. Suckers are planted at 90 x 90 cm spacing.

naadep banaane kee vidhi

taanka bharane kee vidhi :- khaad saamagree pooree tarah ekatrit karane ke baad neeche batae kram anusaar hee taanka bharen. achaar daalane kee tarj par hee naadep padhdati khaad saamagree ek hee din mein ya jyaada se jyaada 48 ghante mein pooree tarah se taanka mein bharakar seel kar den.

pratham bharaee :- taanka bharane se pahale taanke ke andar kee deevaar evan pharsh gobar va paanee ke ghol se achchha geela kar den.

pahalee parat :- vaanaspatik padaarth kachara, danthal, tahaniyaan, pattiaayaan aadi poore taanke mein chh: inch kee oochaee tak bhar den. is 30 ghanapheet mein 100 se 110 kilo vaanaspatik saamagree aaegee. is parat mein 3 se 4 pratishat neem ya palaash kee haree pattiaayaan milaana laabhaprad hoga. jisase deemak par niyantran hoga.

doosaree parat :- gobar ka ghol 125 se 150 leetar paanee mein 4 kilo gobar milaakar pahalee parat ke upar is tarah chhidaken ki pooree vaanaspatik saamagree achchhee tarah bheeg jae. garmee mein paanee kee maatra adhik rakhen. yadi baayogais kee slaree upayog karen to 10 leetar slaree ko 125 se 150 leetar paanee mein ghol kar chhidaken.

teesaree parat :- bheegee huee doosaree patar ke upar, saaph chhanee huee mittee 50 se 60 kilo ke lagabhag samaan roop se bichha den. paraton ke isee kram mein taanke ko usake munh se 1.5 pheet upar tak jhopadeenuma aakaar se bharen. saamaanyat: 11-12 paraton mein taanka bhar jaavega. taanka bharane ke baad taanka seel karane ke lie 3 inch mittee (400 se 500 kilo) kee parat jama kar gobar se leep den. is par daraaren pade to unhe pun: gobar se leep den.
dviteey bharaee :- 15-20 din baad taanke mein bharee saamagree sikud kar 8-9 inch neeche chalee jaavegee tab pahalee bharaee kee tarah hee vaanaspatik padaarth, gobar ka ghol evan chhanee mittee kee paraton se taanke ko unake munh se 1.5 pheet upar tak bharakar pahale bharaav ke samaan hee seel kar leep den.

saavadhaaniyaan :- naadep kampost ko pakane ke liye 90 se 120 din lagate hai. is dauraan namee banee rahane ke lie evan daraare band karane ke lie gobar paanee ka ghol chhidakate rahen va daraaren na padane den. ghaas aadi uge to use ukhaad de va namee kaayam rakhen. kadee dhoop ho to ghaas-phoos se chhaaya kar den.

khaad kee paripakvata :- 3-4 maheene mein khaad gahare bhoore rang kee ban jaatee hai aur durgandh samaapt hokar achchhee khushaboo aatee hai. khaad sookhana nahin chaahiye. is khaad ko ek pheet mein 35 taar vaalee chalanee se chhaan lena chaahiye aur phir upayog mein laana chaahiye. chhalanee ke upar se nikala adhapaka kachcha khaad phir se khaad banaane ke kaam mein lena chaahiye . ek taanke se nikala khaad 6-7 ekad bhoomi ko diya ja sakata hai. ek taanke se 160 se 175 ghan pheet chhana khaad va 40 se 50 ghan pheet kachcha maal milega. matalab ek taanke se 3 tan (lagabhag 6 bailagaadee) achchha paka khaad milata hai.
naadep taanka vidhi se kam se kam gobar mein adhikaadhik maatra mein achchhee gunavattaaa ka khaad taiyaar hota hai. maatr ek gaay ke saal bhar ke gobar se 10 tan khaad milane kee sambhaavana hai. jisamen natrajan 0.5 se 1.5 pratishat sphoor 0.5 se 0.9 pratishat tatha potaash 1.2 se 1.4 pratishat hota hai.
